{"key":"processedPost-5783202","value":{"id":5783202,"first":5782642,"last":5783364,"when":1151072786,"utime":"06/23/06 05:26 PM","content":"Cotton was our old standard for many years for plugging liquid culture flasks, and up until just three or four years ago, stamets was still recommending cotton.  Cotton works fine as long as it stays totally dry.  Polyfil is non-organic, so really is the better choice.  However, make sure the polyfil also stays dry.  Bacteria will colonize right through wet filter material, whether it's organic or not.<br />RR","title":"Re: polyfil and cotton balls! micro tape"}}